{"id":1271,"date":"2010-12-17T06:37:00","date_gmt":"2010-12-17T12:37:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mega_amount_of_triangles.php"},"modified":"2010-12-17T06:37:00","modified_gmt":"2010-12-17T12:37:00","slug":"mega_amount_of_triangles","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mega_amount_of_triangles.php","title":{"rendered":"Mega Amount of Triangles"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mega_tv_logo.gif\" alt=\"Mega Logo, Before and After\"><\/p>\n<p>Originally launched as Red Televisiva Megavisi&oacute;n in 1990, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mega.cl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mega<\/a> is a popular TV channel in Chile, specifically in the capital city of Santiago where it airs, with a mix of news, reality, and sitcoms like a remake of <em>Married%hellip; with Children<\/em> (the Bundys are replaced by the Larra&iacute;ns). In October, Mega introduced a new logo, reportedly designed by local agency Hambre, who were also in charge of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/follow-up_government_of_chile.php\">the recent Chilean government identity<\/a>. (They don&#8217;t have a website I know of, so it&#8217;s hard to corroborate 100%).<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mega_tv_logo_detail.jpg\" alt=\"Mega Logo, Before and After\"><\/p>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"574\" height=\"352\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/5Hahv9SeURs?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"574\" height=\"460\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/C1y16QbFigw?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"574\" height=\"460\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/5Lcwkyemp4U?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">A few random on-air bumpers.<\/p>\n<p>The old logo looked like it belonged in a 1980s 32-inch television that needed a garage to accommodate its rear. Something too techie\/primitive about it that just doesn&#8217;t look too appealing. The new one is fairly trendy &mdash; much like the old one was when it was first used probably &mdash; with a bold, rounded sans serif with stuff in it. The &#8220;stuff&#8221; is standard issue colorful triangles without much rhyme or reason and perhaps there doesn&#8217;t need to be rhyme or reason, just something that looks good on TV. As the bumpers above show, it does look good on TV. The logo isn&#8217;t too spectacular but it doesn&#8217;t deserve the major hatred it&#8217;s been getting from its Chilean audience &mdash; browswing through Facebook and YouTube, the comments towards it are quite unflattering. Sure, it could be better, but it could also be worse. Like the old logo.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to Pablo for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101217_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101217_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101217_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101217_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ 